"spell":
  an arbitrary tree of card applications
"ritual":
  a sequence of left/right card applications
"build":
  given a ritual, construct the spell resulting from performing it on I
"incant":
  given a spell, construct a ritual that builds an extensionally equal spell
"sigil":
  expressions of an untyped lambda calculus extended with spell constants
  and applications can be tagged to declare them imperative WRT a variable
  (i.e., they should not be performed until that var's lambda is applied)
"entangled":
  a variable that occurs free in a sigil
*"compleat":
  a sigil having entangled variables (ant.: *"incompleat")
"unravel":
  perform abstraction elimination
"utter":
  submit a turn
"hear":
  read a turn
